Now Musik, managers of the Sound Sultan estate, have announced collaboration between Naija Ninja and foremost home-grown fashion brand, NACK Apparel, towards the launch of the late icon’s merch line, Sound Sultan Eternal. This is part of the activities to celebrate the late icon’s one-year anniversary. Tagged ‘Nack x Naija Ninja for Sound Sultan design competition, the contest is in line with the late Sultan’s vision of nurturing and empowering young talents. Activities to mark the first anniversary of the beloved music icon kicked off in full gear as the management also announced the release of Sultan’s first post-humous studio release, “Reality Chq”, set to drop in July.   Denzel Essien has emerged as La Mode Magazine Kid of the…     ‘Men who love ladies with big backsides are chronic…     Davido creates legacy in new film for Martell   The competition, inviting entries from all over Nigeria & beyond, is an online contest for the Sound Sultan Eternal (SSE) line of apparel and accessories, which offers fair and equal opportunity to young, up-and-coming fashion graphic designers. Entries opened from May 2 to May 12, with a selection process taking place from the 15th to 18th, and the finale on May 19, where the winners will be announced. Celebrity judges for the online competition are Toke Makinwa, Basketmouth, Baba Dee, and NACK Apparel CEO, Tolulope Akin.